Rarely, Limbaugh was partly right.
The significance of the Statue of Liberty depends entirely on perspective.
Lazarus saw it like poor and exhausted but hopeful immigrants on the ship's deck after a long and trying journey.
He saw it from the point of view of people looking for shelter and a better life.
His Statue of Liberty comforts us by giving hope and welcoming.
