These startups will help your company avoid Uber's mistakes
Amy Errett wanted to measure employee satisfaction in her online store start-up company, but the queries didn't work.
The answers were often vague, useless or even misleading.
Although he assured us that the questionnaires were anonymous, some of the employees were suspicious of them.
"The questions were simply not consistent and objective," Errett says. As her hair care company Madison Reed focuses on the online store. The company has 75 employees.
